reviews_data.review_text: Finally a jazz club in Charlotte where you can actually hear real jazz, not a Taylor Swift cover band or a set list that feels like a wedding reception. I really hope 88’s can keep delivering authentic jazz every night of the week and not sell out like other “jazz” venues have (thanks Middle C and Eddie V’s).
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the kind words. Eighty Eights was built to showcase the soul of Charlotte’s local jazz scene, and we promise that won’t change. We’re committed to delivering the music just as it was meant to be experienced—rooted in authenticity, spontaneity, and soul. Your support means the world to us, and we look forward to seeing you again soon.

reviews_data.review_text: Ive been a barista for 5 years, so I know good coffee. The espresso is excellent and the bar staff and atmosphere match the same level of perfection. Highly recommend for coffee, I'll have to come back to try the drinks.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi, Marissa,

Thank you so much for the kind words! It means a lot coming from someone with your experience in coffee. We’re thrilled you enjoyed the espresso and atmosphere — our team takes pride in both. We’d love to have you back to explore the cocktail side next time. See you soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Amazing atmosphere and chill environment. Adored the experience. The live jazz was everything and the drinks we perfect. 10/10
Awesome vibes, great music, marvelous cocktails
Amazing drinks and performers! Really brings jazz bars up to par. Will come again 🎺🎷
Noele was amazing!!! We loved the live music & atmosphere!!!
Noel served us tonight and we are beyond satisfied with the atmosphere and service!! I got my first pickletini and will definitely be back for more HAHA. Shoutout to Brenda Nova & Company ❤️❤️❤️
such a great vibe! noelle was our bartender and was so kind and made my drink to perfection! highly recommend

Wow, I went there with a buddy last night. Got there 8:30ish and got a great table right up front. There was only one server but she did a nice job covering all the tables. The cocktail quality was just ok but we didn’t mind; the atmosphere and energy was incredible and the band (Judith Porter Quartet) was exceptional.  I’ll definitely come back as this is just up the road from me.  Keep in mind that when you close your tab they add a $10 entrance fee.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thanks for stopping by and sharing your experience! We’re thrilled you enjoyed the music and the energy—Judith Porter Quartet always puts on an amazing show.

And yes, that $10 cover directly supports the incredible live talent we host each night. Just to clarify: on Thursdays and Sundays, it's added to the tab, while on Fridays and Saturdays, it's collected at the door.

We also appreciate your note on the cocktails—we’re always looking to improve. If you're open to sharing more detailed feedback, feel free to email us at hello@eightyeightsclt.com. We'd really value your input.

We look forward to welcoming you back soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Small quaint lounge. Beautiful set-up. Live entertainment!
Small quaint lounge. Beautiful set-up. Live entertainment!
Amazing place to hold an event! Beautiful space and atmosphere. Helpful and accommodating staff. Can’t wait to come again!
Best place for music and cocktails
Excellent venue to unwind and listen to jazz with friends!

This place turned me away for how I was dressed. I was wearing a tie dye shirt and athletic shorts and just wanted to buy a coffee. The guy was very rude and snobby. Find a kinder local coffee and cocktail spot than this place

Hi Gabrielle,
     We’re sorry you had a negative experience. We stop serving coffee at 5pm and enforce a dress code during our cocktail and evening service to promote an elevated experience. We would love to have you back to enjoy our coffee during coffee service. Please shoot us an email at Hello@eightyeightsclt to connect.

reviews_data.review_text: Bad was great. Cool vibe. Would recommend.

This is such an amazing bar! Sophia and Noel brought such an amazing vibe and great drink suggestions. I really enjoyed the ambiance in this bar. I didn’t stay for the live music but it is so chill. I’m just visiting Charlotte but I will be back everytime I’m here :)
Great service, Great Drinks

Awesome drinks!! Friendly staff

The music, atmosphere and drinks were 10/10!!! Special shout out to our servers Taelor and Danika were the absolute best; they were so attentive and really had a great vibe! Can’t wait to come here again!

Taelor was the absolute best waiter for my party. We came for jazz night on a Friday and she was so attentive but also let us enjoy the whole time. The place is an amazing ambiance with great energy. Will 100% come back and recommend
Taelor and Danika were so personable and sweet. Atmosphere was amazing music was incredible. 10/10 will be back!
Taelor and Danica were fantastic, thank you for the top notch service. The ambience was excellent as well.
This was such an amazing experience. Danika and Taelor made it so much better! I will definitely be coming back because of these ladies!!
Our server Taelor was amazing! Great place and great vibes! Amazing place to have a great night!
She was the best host, taylor was amazing and accommodating! Thank you!!!
Loved it! Great atmosphere and great music. Would definitely come back. Just wished they served food.
Beautiful atmosphere energy definitely will be coming back drink had me going too found my spot!
Great live music

This was my first time coming here. The server/bartender had a great recommendation for one of their espresso martinis. It was delicious. The vibes were great and we had just missed the live music, so I will definitely be back to check that out another evening. Very cool on the inside and a great location for a date night.

reviews_data.review_text: First of all, the spot is intimate and sexy! The music is on point and people are sleeping on Charlotte’s natural talent! 88s understands that Charlotte is evolving and trying to get in front of the change! They are at the forefront of that change and the rest of the metro area need to get ready because the changes are happening! This is the spot to be Charlotte! Don’t miss out!
Noel and Justin are the best bartenders. And Taylor is the best waitress . Love this place
Great atmosphere, good acoustics for the live music, drink meh...not worth $15 but still a great vibe

I went to the lounge on the 25th as a first time visitor.  I was in there no more then 20 min. I ordered one glass of cabaret. Bill was $30.23. I asked the bartender what was up. He said he had to charge me a member fee. I thought it insane I wasn't told of this fee before he rang it up.  Then I looked at my card statement 2 days later.  They charged my card a second time for the exact amount
plus an additional dollar $31.23.  The place is unethical.  I didn't get a welcoming feeling from the bartender and they straight ripped me off. $61.43 for a glass of wine. They gonna give me my money back. Cause im gonna raise hell over this. Shame on the greedy as bartender 😕
Cool little jazz club.
Had a blast! Enjoyed the live jazz!

review_questions.Noise level: Loud, but you can still talk

reviews_data.review_text: Came here for all of 30-45 min to enjoy some jazz music and it was amazing! Thoroughly enjoyed the jazz music and the music coming from the speakers once the band departed. All employees offered a kind and pleasant experience - EXCEPT one of the bartenders. He smiled zero times, didn't engage in brief banter (30 seconds max), and then rushed us to pay by stating "I'M BUSY I NEED A CARD." First of all, ew. Second of all, I've been to busier places and still haven't experienced such a rude and unhappy bartender. Now, I understand people have their own personal issues but this is your job and we came to have a good time and pay you. He may need training on keeping an enthusiastic mood when dealing with customers. Anyway, this won't deter me from referring but he will be avoided going forward.

Beautiful atmosphere and was so happy to see it in person. My friend and I arrived early to see the band play, paid the cover and assumed the show hadn’t yet started because the lights were still on and we were the second party in the lounge. I’ve seen the Instagram post and the show normally is in a dim lit atmosphere. There were two groups at the bar, but nonetheless the venue was 4 groups from empty. So with that, we assumed the show didn’t officially start yet.

The band was playing great selections and after each song, we applauded! The manager approached us, nervously, and said something along the lines of we were talking too loudly and it was disruptive to the people or to the band? I’m not sure because the music was even loud for us to hear him so I’m not clear on what he said. In my experience, it’s normal to converse before the show begins, but at that point it just didn’t sit right with us and so we left.

Eighty Eights Coffee and Cocktails has been on my radar for months, and it absolutely lived up to the hype! Word to the wise: this place fills up fast, so arrive early. As a huge music fan, especially of jazz, I was thrilled to finally experience the live band - they were phenomenal! As an instrumentalist myself, I have a deep appreciation for live performances, and they truly delivered.

Oh and the staff? Simply AMAZING!
The service was top notch. I mean the staff know what they are doing and you can tell they experienced. My Lemon Drop was delicious and the Dirty Pickletini (a clever twist on a dirty martini) was a delightful surprise. I loved every sip!

Eighty Eights Coffee and Cocktails is a must-visit for anyone who appreciates great music, a cool atmosphere, and top-notch drinks.

Thank you for making my birthday celebration amazing. I will absolutely be back!

First time here. We were seated closer to the back. Atmosphere was nothing like I expected: guests around us were screaming from the top of their lungs during conversations. I get it, this is not a concert, I expected quiet conversations. Instead, we were treated to awesome live jazz drowned by people shouting in each other faces. Disappointing to say the least.
Super cute cover charge is added to your bill so don’t be surprised when you see the random $10 music is great you can even get a little sway in if you wanted

reviews_data.review_text:
I went with my coworker.
Great ambiance, the atmosphere was comfortable & relaxing. I loved the live music

This place is very cool. The music was great! Our server was very friendly. However, it took at least half an hour for her to take or drink order and after waiting 15-20 more minutes after our order was taken, she came back and apologized and said it was taking long because something was wrong with the printer. When they did come, my friend, who asked for extra cherries in her drink, did not have a single cherry. It was also pretty pricey (2 beers, one cocktail, and 2 hidden covers was over $60), and they don't tell you there's a cover, it's added to your drink tab. I don't mind paying a cover, but it seemed kind of sneaky not to even mention it. I would go back for the music and atmosphere. Hopefully, it was just an off night for them.

Wow. What an addition to Charlotte. I am also a big fan of Rosie’s (they have the same owners). This is fantastic vibes and great drinks. On Thursdays-Sundays there is a $10 cover added to your bill for the live music but it is absolutely worth it!!
The music, service and atmosphere have no equal in Charlotte.  This is a very well run club!

This place is absolutely awesome. We were treated to a great musical experience (D. Friday Trio). The wait staff were very attentive, and even when the place was packed, my glass was never empty for more than 5 minutes. The crowd was beautifully mixed with all ages and races, but the VIBE was just where it needed to be. Folks were dancing and having a great time. It brings a smile to my face, reliving the experience as I write this review the following morning. Offering small plates or appetizers would make this the perfect 10 instead of the 9.5 I had to rate it. You must give Eighty Eights a try, you will not be disappointed!!!!!!
Great new live music venue (only jazz). A bit small but very cozy. Awesome drinks and service. No food.
Nice location, good parking. Absolutely no food so be careful consuming alcoholic beverages. Not a Jazz Fan but music was good.
Great French 75s and live jazz!
Crazy line, had to buy tickets, wasn’t disclosed.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your feedback. We’re sorry to hear that your experience wasn’t as expected. Our $10 cover fee is clearly mentioned on both our website and social media pages, and payment is collected by our security team at the door, as usual. We apologize if there was any confusion. If you have any further questions or concerns, feel free to email us at hello@eightyeightsclt.com.

reviews_data.review_text: Great place to catch live jazz in a classy environment

The female server was very pleasant. Unlike the male server who brought me a vodka club soda in a tall glass and told me it’s the same as the short glass.  While it maybe same amount of vodka. The tall glass has more soda than I wanted.  The female server fixed it !

A nice bar!
They have live jazz music

Been in twice in the last month and 10/10 experience both times. Arrived shortly before the music starts at 8, thinking we’d stay for an hour or two, and ended up staying til the end both times. The musicians they bring in are amazing. The vibes are just right. Charlotte was in need of something like this and they absolutely smashed it. Can’t wait to go again.

This place has a very relaxed, intimate vibe. The Jazz Music was very good the evening I went. I'm doing dry January and the Mocktail Old Fashioned was great as far as Mocktails go. It's definitely a nice place for a date night. Will make this a regular spot to enjoy. Only negative is they don't have any food offerings so eat before you go there.
Everything was nice, except the customer service wasn’t all that. It wasn’t a busy night for it to have been the way it was.

Walked in at 3pm on Saturday, excited to check out a place we have not been to before.  No patrons there which was fine considering how early.  The female working barely showed interest in helping us even though we were the only one’s there.  She was on her computer and it felt like we were bothering her.  We stood in silence at the bar with her just looking at us.  We just left without ordering.  Last night we went out to 2 other establishments and raved over not just the drinks but THE SERVICE.  It is important to make a patron feel welcome.  Will not be back.  One person can really make a difference. Shame, my girl was bringing me there as a late Christmas present, it looked like a great establishment.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Aaron,

Thank you for sharing your feedback. We’re truly sorry to hear about your experience and apologize that our service didn’t meet your expectations. This doesn’t reflect the standard we strive for, and we sincerely regret that your first visit was not as it should have been.

Please reach out to us at hello@eightyeightsclt.com so we can make things right.

We’d love the opportunity to welcome you back.

reviews_data.review_text: First visit was for live jazz on a Friday night. The spot is nice—great musicians and sound, mixed and chill crowd, attentive staff, good drinks that aren’t overly fussy. They feature almost 10 espresso drinks on the menu for those who are into that vibe.

It was too cold to stand outside so we ended up leaving. Yes we arrived an hour early.... oh well. Maybe in the future I'll see inside and update my review. reviews_data.review_text: Just FYI this place IS first come first serve so get here early . Also , they do charge 10$ a person during jazz night to pay the performers so do not complain about that . The drinks and service amazing. The atmosphere wonderful. The only reason I’m not giving it 5 stars is because they do not serve tapas or small plates that would surly give  them an edge!
Classy, fabulous, great music, great cocktails, and a great vibe. Highly recommend.
No food served here yet but a beautiful place to relax and listen to  jazz music.

Went here on a whim with some girlfriends. Had such a great time! The vibe is that of a speakeasy / jazz club . Felt very old school Harlem. So I felt right at home. The music was great, the service was great. And the drinks were amazing . It is first come first serve in regard to seating. A cute place for a date night or a nice stop in after work for some live music. I will definitely be back.

I had the worst experience at this place tonight. Stood in line and waited for about 20 minutes since the place was at capacity. I was fine with that. I went there alone. Paid $10 admission. When I got inside, the host took me to a table where I had to stand. She told me that more people would likely be brought to my table to stand with me which I was fine with. Then I saw one of the tables cleared. Then some ladies that came in about 10 minutes after I did, were lead to the table where they were seated. I waved down the host and asked her why people who came in after me were granted a seat. She told me that because I was alone, I had to stand while the party of 2 ladies was able to sit down at a table. This was one of the worst experiences I’ve had in Charlotte to date. Since I was alone, I had to stand but since there were 2 of them, they could sit. Does this sound right? I will NEVER be back. EVER.
Stopped in for coffee on a Sunday afternoon. Delightful staff and atmosphere. Definitely making this my go-to coffee spot in the area and can’t wait to come check out the nightlife

a party of 10 came in and we loved our experience up until the end… our waiter never explained how the payment was done, we asked to be placed on separate tabs, but he explained they’d be split up afterwards.

We assumed it’d be an itemized bill, but it wasn’t, so it was charged and split 5 different ways… this system is a very poor and expensive system. The waiter was very rude and disrespectful and saying things like “you see this screen, there’s no option for itemizing” in a very condescending way… we paid and then the manger came up and then said we could itemize it but it has to be done at the front… we wish this was communicated before we paid… it It’s not right to charge others who only buy one drink $65+ when they only bought one drink.

It doesn’t make any sense that we couldn’t split up the bill itemized, especially when we asked to do that prior to even getting any drinks. Why are we expected to pay for other peoples drinks when only purchasing one or two drinks.

I really enjoyed the atmosphere and the experience, but this paying system is not right or fair to groups of friends visiting. It made us not wait to come back after the waiter experience and having to pay for other people’s drinks.

I hope this issue gets resolved.

I love jazz clubs and was so excited to try out this new establishment and it didn’t disappoint! Love the vibe inside, staff was so accommodating and attentive and the band was great. We were waiting outside and management was able to pull up two chairs for us and find us a place to sit, which was so unexpected and kind. There is a $10 cover, which is a generous alternative to purchasing tickets. I do wish they had some small plates. This is such a great addition to Charlotte and the arts/music scene. We had the absolute best time and will 100% be back!!

Super fun
Awesome music

This place is a whole vibe! Drinks were great and our server was lovely. This is the only thing that did not make sense to me: We were a group of seven that came in at around 7:30 and then about maybe about an hour and a half into being there, our server let us know that a $10 cover charge was added to our tabs because they start charging a cover after a certain time. In the grand scheme of things, $10 is not a lot of money, but it does not seem ethical to charge people a cover charge when they were already inside the establishment long before the cover is implemented. I feel like this can deter people from coming altogether. I will be back, but I think management needs to rethink on this because nowhere else does this.

I really wanted to love this place! We excitedly waited outside in the cold for about 35-40 minutes. Thank God for the heaters! The gentlemen at the front kept checking in with us letting us know they were working on it which we really appreciated. The hostess came out and let him know there was a table for us but they were cleaning it up. A couple then walked up to the rope unchained it and walked in. He greeted the gentlemen at the front and walked inside. Turns out we now no longer had a table ready for us and had to wait some more. As we waited some more we witnessed several people walking up and walking inside or being able to walk in if their party was inside so that made the wait even longer. After about another 20-25 minutes the lady stepped out talked to him and told us she was cleaning our table off. Finally it was our turn! We were ready to get inside have a seat and enjoy some good music. He charged us our $10 per person and we headed in! As we walked in the hostess let us know our table was in the back corner. As we walked over we realize it is just a tall table in the corner for us to stand around. Not once did he mention we would be standing or asked if it was ok. Earlier he had offered a seat at the bar with one of us standing and we said we’d rather wait so we were highly confused. Another table was beside us and a party of four was sent there so now I couldn’t even see anything and on top of that the window although covered was still radiating cold air so I was still freezing. After 10 minutes we were bummed and decided to head out. Not sure if we’ll give it another try in the future but if you do be ready to wait and watch several people skip in front of you. 😔
Awesome lil spot I got coffee at and chatted with the bartender when I came to look for apartments. Will be back since I am moving in down the street!
Don't come for a night cap...last call is 30 mins before close.
Chai was excellent can’t wait to come back for cocktails- this place will be bumping soon.

this place is exactly what charlotte needed! the drinks are so delicious, the music is great all the time & parking is free. the vibes are so cool & it’s the spot. there’s a cover for the band & no food & it’s still really great!
Very calm place to relax, listen to great music live, & grab a drink.

Well I taken me a minute to write this review what am going to say this .From the amazing security team member to the welcoming young lady with the bob cute cut to the amazing I mean amazing Bartender guess forgive for forgetting your name Queen .I love your dread you rock Queen you made me and my fiance date night magically you paid closer attention to detail with no problem .I didn’t need to give you instructions on what and how much .I feel in love with drink as a person who often dissatisfied with drinks.When we order drinks out .I felt I made that drink you had us coming back for more drinks .We had the best time ever the atmosphere and the live music had us dancing and singing and laughing and have a blast.We were thanked for coming and the security team member he assisted from the beginning to the end .Thank us for coming this a gem you most experience .I will recommend you come early since they have limited seating .I went on Saturday night so you are a party of two bar area great larger group get a table .They don’t have reservations but be aware you 10.00 including in your final bill

EXCELLENT SERVICE. Everyone working here was so kind and went above and beyond. Even though they were at capacity and beyond busy it never felt like anyone around us was in a rush. Drinks were delish and I loved the mocktail I tried. Music was beautiful and the interior was stunning!
Music is great if you love Jazz. The experience is delightful. Drinks may take a lot of time after the show has started because the space is small. I'll definitely be back.
I don’t even like coffee but this is best coffee/bar I have ever seen. Clean, easy parking, love it! I’ll be back weekly 😆
We go for the music, drinks, and atmosphere! This place has quickly made it to the top of my favorites list.
This is exactly what Charlotte needed! The vibe, music, and people are awesome. Highly recommend.
Unbelievable vibes and awesome cocktails! One of a kind place
Bringing back the elegant jazz bar vibe that our culture needs. Talented musicians, delicious cocktails, and sharp dressed individuals
One of my favorite new places in charlotte for drinks and live music. Jazz fans this place is a must.
This place is just what was missing in the neighborhood.  It’s the perfect spot to go for a cocktail after or before dinner.  We had so much fun and are already looking forward to going again soon!
The best of the best! Shout out Ben M for the vibes.
Nice spot in an up and coming area, happy to have you in our community! Drinks were awesome, ambiance was perfect for Jazz - great layout & ‘Mad Men’ type of vibe

This jazz bar is a hidden gem! The cozy, vintage vibe, live music, and fair drink prices make it the perfect spot for a night out. Talented musicians bring jazz and blues to life, and the bartender – a true gentleman who even knows how to play piano – adds to the charm. The atmosphere is relaxed and inviting. Whether you’re a jazz fan or just out for a great evening, this place hits all the right notes!

Atmosphere and drinks were great as was the music.  But all in all my group of 5 people didn't have a great experience. We waited at the patio table outside for an hour and 10 mins (November weather) and were told we were next on the seating list. We watched multiple parties who showed up after us get seated. We then were told, after asking if we were still on the list for a table, that they did community seat. Honestly, they had no table accommodating parties for more than 4. We were moved to a standing cocktail table and then waited another hour to be offered a seating table. At this point we had waited 2 hours to be offered a table. What really got us, was when we got the itemized receipt, after paying AND tipping, was they included a cover of $10 per person in the total. We were not told there was a cover and had no idea this would be included in the grand total. We tipped for a cover, which is unnecessary. We felt this was sneaky. Servers were great, management wouldn't look at us while waiting to be seated and we felt as if we weren't communicative enough about still wanting a table. This place has potential, but won't be returning for a while.
The management and bouncer are beyond rude!!! I would stay clear of this establishment. Do not recommend. Plenty of other places in CLT to enjoy drinks at. 😉
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Elizabeth, 
We take customer service seriously and strive to create a positive experience for all guests. We stand by our policies and expect all guests to adhere to them for the safety and enjoyment of everyone. If you'd like to discuss your experience further, please feel free to reach out to us directly : hello@eightyeightsclt.com 
Thank you!

reviews_data.review_text: I met my homegirl at the jazz spot to hear live music. We didn't research before hand, but later realized they do not sell food. Only wines, cocktails, and mocktails. The music was fantastic. There's a $10 cover that helps pay the musicians. This visit was a busy one; barely a place to sit. There's a free parking lot. The area is nice and quiet. My new obsession is the matcha cocktail made by Noele. It’s soo tasty and has a nice little kick. I’ll definitely be back for more!
No food.. wonderful atmosphere..

reviews_data.review_text: I love this place. A nice amount of parking. The band was amazing and they had very friendly staff, bartenders, and owners. The drinks are very tasty and they keep them flowing. I will be back for many many nights!

If food were served, I am certain it would be "5 star," as is everything else about this establishment: staff, atmosphere, music!   I just found out about this place, and am so grateful that they are saving me the travel cost of going to NYC to find a LEGIT Jazz Lounge!! The weekends are booked with various different groups, but the Thursday night "House Band" - the John Shaughnessy Trio - is not to be missed: John Shaughnessy on Bass, John Spurrier on Drums, and Phil Howe on Piano.  I look forward to hearing some great jazz here in the future!!
What a fantastic place for a fun date night! Food, drinks and staff are all great and the vibe is on point… we’ll be going often!

Incredible opening nights! I'm so excited for this new bar and coffee shop in the Sugar Creek area! Great cocktails and attentive staff, the music was great and the seating was comfortable! it will be a great space to hang out and work at with coffee during the day.

EDIT: Coffee is great! They use CLT roaster Pure Intentions. They have a quiet  coffee house ambiance  in the mornings, would be a great place to get some remote work or reading done!

reviews_data.review_text:
A Perfect Night Out in Charlotte

I had the opportunity to check out Eighty Eights Jazz and Wine Bar on a Saturday night, and it was a fantastic experience. My party and I arrived around 9:30 pm and had to wait in line outside, but the wait was less than ten minutes. The bouncer was super friendly and kept us informed the whole time, which was a nice touch. As people left, their tables were promptly cleaned, and the next group was allowed inside. Once seated, we had a great view of the stage, though I’m confident there’s not a bad seat in the house.

We had some unexpected company join us, and the staff was incredibly accommodating, quickly adding seats to our table without a hitch. Despite the packed house, it was clear everyone was having a blast—enjoying the live jazz, drinks, and great company. Our waitress came around to take our drink orders and checked in periodically throughout the night. You could tell she was managing multiple tables, but she did an excellent job ensuring we were all set and having a good time.

My only recommendation, and this is purely personal, is to offer more water options beyond just tap and sparkling (I can be a bit of a water snob!). That said, it didn’t take away from the experience—just something to consider.

Overall, Eighty Eights is a wonderful spot to visit, especially on weekends for live music or during the week when they’re open in the evenings starting on Thursdays. I’m also looking forward to visiting during the day to work remotely and try their coffee. It’s great to see Charlotte growing as a hub for evening activities. A quick side note: they don’t serve food, so be sure to grab dinner beforehand.

I recently celebrated my birthday at this jazz club, and it turned out to be an unforgettable experience. The live jazz music was nothing short of phenomenal, with talented musicians creating an atmosphere that was both lively and soulful. The service truly stood out, as the staff was attentive and friendly, and my drinks arrived surprisingly quickly.

A special shoutout to Kiva, the mixologist with the green hair, who added a unique flair to the evening. Her cocktails were expertly crafted and arrived with a smile, making each drink as memorable as the music. One of the highlights was the opportunity to sit with new people and mingle in a warm, welcoming environment. It was easy to strike up conversations, and the club’s open vibe made everyone feel like part of the scene.

I’m already planning my next visit—even if it’s just for a morning coffee. This place has a magnetic charm that goes beyond the music, and Kiva’s artistry behind the bar is just one more reason to return.
It's a great place to either start your day with coffee or end it with a cocktail.  The vibe is great, and the live music amazing

Went Saturday with 3 friends, got there at 7 to get a seat for the 8pm show. The drummer was super fantastic and the decor was nice. However, if you don't plan on ordering more than one drink or nursing that one drink all night you may be asked to get up from your table and stand if you intend on saying for the rest of the show or evening. You guessed it, we were asked to leave our table if we were not going to consume anymore drinks. They did try to be subtle by cleaning off the table, closing out our tab (no split checks here), and wishing us a good night several times. When that didn't work the hostess came over and politely explained they needed the table for paying customers...didn't we just pay??? Anyway, we left mid-set and didn't get to hear the rest of that fantastic drummer. My advice...nurse your drink or lose your seat!

Long line, but they select who can cut. Waited 30 min and witnessed MANY be allowed in since they were “fellow bar
owners” felt like a frat party as they picked who could enter
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Greta, 
Thank you for sharing your experience with us. We truly appreciate your feedback and apologize for the wait you encountered. We aim to provide a welcoming environment for all our guests, and we regret that it felt exclusive for others during your visit.

To ensure a more enjoyable experience on your next visit, please send us a email to hello@eightyeightsclt.com with your experience, so we can try to make it right. 

We thank you for your understanding, and we hope to see you soon.

reviews_data.review_text: Beautiful shop, amazing coffee, friendly staff and atmosphere is super cozy. 10/10 recommend!

Beautiful spot with incredible potential..only reason gave 4 out of 5 for atmosphere if you are a music lover the loud chatter made it a lil hard to fully enjoy the artist...the espresso martini was one of BEST I have ever had

Kiara was an amazing manager and was super welcoming! The drinks were fantastic and the wait was not too long. The music was great and our group highly recommends!

CALLING ALL JAZZ LOVERS!! Charlotte has welcomed this amazing new cocktail jazz lounge and let me tell you, it’s a whole vibe! Best of all….NO cover charge! the service was great, drinks tasty and music amazing! They open at 5 for the 21+ crowd for cocktails, and live band starts at 8. They will eventually have coffee shop items during the day. I highly recommend getting there early to find a seat because the place is small and intimate. There is free parking but the lot and streets can fill up quick. I’m so glad Charlotte now has a chill lounge to relax in without being limited to a ticketed show that only last for abt an hr and half like other jazz venues.
This place is beautiful! Amazing drinks and great vibe all around. Excited to see other musicians they bring in!
Awesome drinks, will be my new favorite spot. The bartenders are friendly. The drinks are tasty and the live music is great!

**Review: A Hidden Gem for Jazz and Cocktails**

I recently had the pleasure of visiting this spot- a newly opened jazz bar that effortlessly combines smooth tunes with expertly crafted cocktails. Tucked away in a cozy corner of the city, this place offers an intimate setting perfect for unwinding after a long day or for a special night out.

The ambiance is warm and inviting, with dim lighting, vintage decor, and plush seating that evokes a classic jazz club feel. The sound of live jazz fills the room, with talented musicians playing everything from bebop to soulful ballads. The acoustics are fantastic, allowing the music to be a centerpiece without overwhelming conversation.

The cocktail menu is a standout feature. Each drink is thoughtfully crafted, with a balance of creative flair and classic sensibility.

What sets them apart is the attention to detail—whether it’s the impeccable service, the beautifully garnished drinks, or the perfectly timed jazz sets. The staff is knowledgeable and attentive, happy to recommend drinks based on your preferences or to chat about the evening’s performers. Kiara and Ben were incredible! Can’t wait to see what they do with the place.

If you’re looking for a spot that offers the best of both worlds—delicious cocktails and authentic live jazz..It’s a refreshing addition to the local scene, and I’m excited to see it become a go-to destination for jazz lovers and cocktail enthusiasts alike.

Captivating, moody aesthetic that perfectly sets the stage for an intimate night out. The staff is warm and attentive, enhancing the overall experience with their genuine hospitality. Coupled with smooth live performances, it's a must-visit
This is the new hotspot in Charlotte! Get there early, your friends are already there!
Fantastic drinks, music, and atmosphere!

This place is great! The drinks are delicious, and the staff is so friendly and attentive. Such an awesome place with a super cool ambiance. And the jazz adds such a vibe 😍. I will definitely be a regular at 88s!
Great energy, great cocktails, amazing staff!! Loved the music and entertainment. Can't wait to see the performers this place brings in!
Charlotte’s best kept secret! Had the best time sipping martinis and lounging with friends. If you love jazz music and chill vibes this is the place.
Great drink menu and really cool atmosphere. Thankful to have a piano bar now in Charlotte!
What a fun place to bring to Charlotte! Loved the ambiance, drinks, and music! Will definitely be back
Great Vibes! The best martini in town 🖤
Just what Charlotte needed. Great atmosphere and people. Well done
Atmosphere was great, drinks were delicious!

Amazing new spot in Charlotte! Having a jazz music option in a busy city with a lot of sports-focused bars is such a wonderful concept. And the menu is so well curated, serving both elevated alcoholic AND non-alcoholic beverages. Excited for more nights here!!!
Incredible staff and absolutely beautiful atmosphere!! Can't wait to go back!
Incredible staff and absolutely beautiful atmosphere!! Can't wait to go back!

what an AMAZING opening night! with large crowds, the team was still able to keep tables clean, fresh drinks in people’s hands either at the bar or by table service.  so thankful to have a jazz bar in clt!!! the ambiance was perfect and made it a perfect night out. can’t wait to come back!

What an amazing grand opening night! The music was incredible, the diversity of guests was amazing, and the staff was absolutely rocking it! Busy, and worth the wait. Planning my next night out here! And so excited to come during the day for a chill coffee vibe! ☕️
Incredible cocktail bar with a varying selection of craft cocktails and super knowledgeable bartenders. Everyone is super sweet, and ready to offer suggestions based on your palate. Phenomenal!
The vibes were on point. Had a great time! Will be back soon :)

What a great opening night! The team showed up with the energy while the bar was slammed with drinks. The espresso martinis are to die for, love the atmosphere, looking forward to the jazz bands in the evenings. So glad Charlotte has this new gem!

Waited another 45 minutes sitting at the bar and never received our drinks.   Asked twice and both times were told they were the next drinks up.

reviews_data.review_text: Finally a jazz club in Charlotte where you can actually hear real jazz, not a Taylor Swift cover band or a set list that feels like a wedding reception. I really hope 88’s can keep delivering authentic jazz every night of the week and not sell out like other “jazz” venues have (thanks Middle C and Eddie V’s).
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the kind words. Eighty Eights was built to showcase the soul of Charlotte’s local jazz scene, and we promise that won’t change. We’re committed to delivering the music just as it was meant to be experienced—rooted in authenticity, spontaneity, and soul. Your support means the world to us, and we look forward to seeing you again soon.

reviews_data.review_text: Ive been a barista for 5 years, so I know good coffee. The espresso is excellent and the bar staff and atmosphere match the same level of perfection. Highly recommend for coffee, I'll have to come back to try the drinks.

reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thanks for stopping by and sharing your experience! We’re thrilled you enjoyed the music and the energy—Judith Porter Quartet always puts on an amazing show.

And yes, that $10 cover directly supports the incredible live talent we host each night. Just to clarify: on Thursdays and Sundays, it's added to the tab, while on Fridays and Saturdays, it's collected at the door.

We also appreciate your note on the cocktails—we’re always looking to improve. If you're open to sharing more detailed feedback, feel free to email us at hello@eightyeightsclt.com. We'd really value your input.

We look forward to welcoming you back soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Came here for all of 30-45 min to enjoy some jazz music and it was amazing! Thoroughly enjoyed the jazz music and the music coming from the speakers once the band departed. All employees offered a kind and pleasant experience - EXCEPT one of the bartenders. He smiled zero times, didn't engage in brief banter (30 seconds max), and then rushed us to pay by stating "I'M BUSY I NEED A CARD." First of all, ew. Second of all, I've been to busier places and still haven't experienced such a rude and unhappy bartender. Now, I understand people have their own personal issues but this is your job and we came to have a good time and pay you. He may need training on keeping an enthusiastic mood when dealing with customers. Anyway, this won't deter me from referring but he will be avoided going forward.

Beautiful atmosphere and was so happy to see it in person. My friend and I arrived early to see the band play, paid the cover and assumed the show hadn’t yet started because the lights were still on and we were the second party in the lounge. I’ve seen the Instagram post and the show normally is in a dim lit atmosphere. There were two groups at the bar, but nonetheless the venue was 4 groups from empty. So with that, we assumed the show didn’t officially start yet.

The band was playing great selections and after each song, we applauded! The manager approached us, nervously, and said something along the lines of we were talking too loudly and it was disruptive to the people or to the band? I’m not sure because the music was even loud for us to hear him so I’m not clear on what he said. In my experience, it’s normal to converse before the show begins, but at that point it just didn’t sit right with us and so we left.

Eighty Eights Coffee and Cocktails has been on my radar for months, and it absolutely lived up to the hype! Word to the wise: this place fills up fast, so arrive early. As a huge music fan, especially of jazz, I was thrilled to finally experience the live band - they were phenomenal! As an instrumentalist myself, I have a deep appreciation for live performances, and they truly delivered.

Oh and the staff? Simply AMAZING!
The service was top notch. I mean the staff know what they are doing and you can tell they experienced. My Lemon Drop was delicious and the Dirty Pickletini (a clever twist on a dirty martini) was a delightful surprise. I loved every sip!

Eighty Eights Coffee and Cocktails is a must-visit for anyone who appreciates great music, a cool atmosphere, and top-notch drinks.

Thank you for making my birthday celebration amazing. I will absolutely be back!

First time here. We were seated closer to the back. Atmosphere was nothing like I expected: guests around us were screaming from the top of their lungs during conversations. I get it, this is not a concert, I expected quiet conversations. Instead, we were treated to awesome live jazz drowned by people shouting in each other faces. Disappointing to say the least.

I went with my coworker.
Great ambiance, the atmosphere was comfortable & relaxing. I loved the live music

This place is very cool. The music was great! Our server was very friendly. However, it took at least half an hour for her to take or drink order and after waiting 15-20 more minutes after our order was taken, she came back and apologized and said it was taking long because something was wrong with the printer. When they did come, my friend, who asked for extra cherries in her drink, did not have a single cherry. It was also pretty pricey (2 beers, one cocktail, and 2 hidden covers was over $60), and they don't tell you there's a cover, it's added to your drink tab. I don't mind paying a cover, but it seemed kind of sneaky not to even mention it. I would go back for the music and atmosphere. Hopefully, it was just an off night for them.

Wow. What an addition to Charlotte. I am also a big fan of Rosie’s (they have the same owners). This is fantastic vibes and great drinks. On Thursdays-Sundays there is a $10 cover added to your bill for the live music but it is absolutely worth it!!

This place is absolutely awesome. We were treated to a great musical experience (D. Friday Trio). The wait staff were very attentive, and even when the place was packed, my glass was never empty for more than 5 minutes. The crowd was beautifully mixed with all ages and races, but the VIBE was just where it needed to be. Folks were dancing and having a great time. It brings a smile to my face, reliving the experience as I write this review the following morning. Offering small plates or appetizers would make this the perfect 10 instead of the 9.5 I had to rate it. You must give Eighty Eights a try, you will not be disappointed!!!!!!

The female working barely showed interest in helping us even though we were the only one’s there.  She was on her computer and it felt like we were bothering her. It is important to make a patron feel welcome.  Will not be back.  One person can really make a difference. Shame, my girl was bringing me there as a late Christmas present, it looked like a great establishment.

Went here on a whim with some girlfriends. Had such a great time! The vibe is that of a speakeasy / jazz club . Felt very old school Harlem. So I felt right at home. The music was great, the service was great. And the drinks were amazing . It is first come first serve in regard to seating. A cute place for a date night or a nice stop in after work for some live music. I will definitely be back.

I had the worst experience at this place tonight. Stood in line and waited for about 20 minutes since the place was at capacity. I was fine with that. I went there alone. Paid $10 admission. When I got inside, the host took me to a table where I had to stand. She told me that more people would likely be brought to my table to stand with me which I was fine with. Then I saw one of the tables cleared. Then some ladies that came in about 10 minutes after I did, were lead to the table where they were seated. I waved down the host and asked her why people who came in after me were granted a seat. She told me that because I was alone, I had to stand while the party of 2 ladies was able to sit down at a table. This was one of the worst experiences I’ve had in Charlotte to date. Since I was alone, I had to stand but since there were 2 of them, they could sit. Does this sound right? I will NEVER be back. EVER.
Stopped in for coffee on a Sunday afternoon. Delightful staff and atmosphere. Definitely making this my go-to coffee spot in the area and can’t wait to come check out the nightlife

a party of 10 came in and we loved our experience up until the end… our waiter never explained how the payment was done, we asked to be placed on separate tabs, but he explained they’d be split up afterwards.

We assumed it’d be an itemized bill, but it wasn’t, so it was charged and split 5 different ways… this system is a very poor and expensive system. The waiter was very rude and disrespectful and saying things like “you see this screen, there’s no option for itemizing” in a very condescending way… we paid and then the manger came up and then said we could itemize it but it has to be done at the front… we wish this was communicated before we paid… it It’s not right to charge others who only buy one drink $65+ when they only bought one drink.

It doesn’t make any sense that we couldn’t split up the bill itemized, especially when we asked to do that prior to even getting any drinks. Why are we expected to pay for other peoples drinks when only purchasing one or two drinks.

I really enjoyed the atmosphere and the experience, but this paying system is not right or fair to groups of friends visiting. It made us not wait to come back after the waiter experience and having to pay for other people’s drinks.

I hope this issue gets resolved.

I love jazz clubs and was so excited to try out this new establishment and it didn’t disappoint! Love the vibe inside, staff was so accommodating and attentive and the band was great. We were waiting outside and management was able to pull up two chairs for us and find us a place to sit, which was so unexpected and kind. There is a $10 cover, which is a generous alternative to purchasing tickets. I do wish they had some small plates. This is such a great addition to Charlotte and the arts/music scene. We had the absolute best time and will 100% be back!!

Super fun
Awesome music

This place is a whole vibe! Drinks were great and our server was lovely. This is the only thing that did not make sense to me: We were a group of seven that came in at around 7:30 and then about maybe about an hour and a half into being there, our server let us know that a $10 cover charge was added to our tabs because they start charging a cover after a certain time. In the grand scheme of things, $10 is not a lot of money, but it does not seem ethical to charge people a cover charge when they were already inside the establishment long before the cover is implemented. I feel like this can deter people from coming altogether. I will be back, but I think management needs to rethink on this because nowhere else does this.

I really wanted to love this place! We excitedly waited outside in the cold for about 35-40 minutes. Thank God for the heaters! The gentlemen at the front kept checking in with us letting us know they were working on it which we really appreciated. The hostess came out and let him know there was a table for us but they were cleaning it up. A couple then walked up to the rope unchained it and walked in. He greeted the gentlemen at the front and walked inside. Turns out we now no longer had a table ready for us and had to wait some more. As we waited some more we witnessed several people walking up and walking inside or being able to walk in if their party was inside so that made the wait even longer. After about another 20-25 minutes the lady stepped out talked to him and told us she was cleaning our table off. Finally it was our turn! We were ready to get inside have a seat and enjoy some good music. He charged us our $10 per person and we headed in! As we walked in the hostess let us know our table was in the back corner. As we walked over we realize it is just a tall table in the corner for us to stand around. Not once did he mention we would be standing or asked if it was ok. Earlier he had offered a seat at the bar with one of us standing and we said we’d rather wait so we were highly confused. Another table was beside us and a party of four was sent there so now I couldn’t even see anything and on top of that the window although covered was still radiating cold air so I was still freezing. After 10 minutes we were bummed and decided to head out. Not sure if we’ll give it another try in the future but if you do be ready to wait and watch several people skip in front of you. 😔
Awesome lil spot I got coffee at and chatted with the bartender when I came to look for apartments. Will be back since I am moving in down the street!
Don't come for a night cap...last call is 30 mins before close.
Chai was excellent can’t wait to come back for cocktails- this place will be bumping soon.

reviews_data.review_text:
A Perfect Night Out in Charlotte

I had the opportunity to check out Eighty Eights Jazz and Wine Bar on a Saturday night, and it was a fantastic experience. My party and I arrived around 9:30 pm and had to wait in line outside, but the wait was less than ten minutes. The bouncer was super friendly and kept us informed the whole time, which was a nice touch. As people left, their tables were promptly cleaned, and the next group was allowed inside. Once seated, we had a great view of the stage, though I’m confident there’s not a bad seat in the house.

We had some unexpected company join us, and the staff was incredibly accommodating, quickly adding seats to our table without a hitch. Despite the packed house, it was clear everyone was having a blast—enjoying the live jazz, drinks, and great company. Our waitress came around to take our drink orders and checked in periodically throughout the night. You could tell she was managing multiple tables, but she did an excellent job ensuring we were all set and having a good time.

My only recommendation, and this is purely personal, is to offer more water options beyond just tap and sparkling (I can be a bit of a water snob!). That said, it didn’t take away from the experience—just something to consider.

Overall, Eighty Eights is a wonderful spot to visit, especially on weekends for live music or during the week when they’re open in the evenings starting on Thursdays. I’m also looking forward to visiting during the day to work remotely and try their coffee. It’s great to see Charlotte growing as a hub for evening activities. A quick side note: they don’t serve food, so be sure to grab dinner beforehand.

I recently celebrated my birthday at this jazz club, and it turned out to be an unforgettable experience. The live jazz music was nothing short of phenomenal, with talented musicians creating an atmosphere that was both lively and soulful. The service truly stood out, as the staff was attentive and friendly, and my drinks arrived surprisingly quickly.

A special shoutout to Kiva, the mixologist with the green hair, who added a unique flair to the evening. Her cocktails were expertly crafted and arrived with a smile, making each drink as memorable as the music. One of the highlights was the opportunity to sit with new people and mingle in a warm, welcoming environment. It was easy to strike up conversations, and the club’s open vibe made everyone feel like part of the scene.

I’m already planning my next visit—even if it’s just for a morning coffee. This place has a magnetic charm that goes beyond the music, and Kiva’s artistry behind the bar is just one more reason to return.
It's a great place to either start your day with coffee or end it with a cocktail.  The vibe is great, and the live music amazing

Went Saturday with 3 friends, got there at 7 to get a seat for the 8pm show. The drummer was super fantastic and the decor was nice. However, if you don't plan on ordering more than one drink or nursing that one drink all night you may be asked to get up from your table and stand if you intend on saying for the rest of the show or evening. You guessed it, we were asked to leave our table if we were not going to consume anymore drinks. They did try to be subtle by cleaning off the table, closing out our tab (no split checks here), and wishing us a good night several times. When that didn't work the hostess came over and politely explained they needed the table for paying customers...didn't we just pay??? Anyway, we left mid-set and didn't get to hear the rest of that fantastic drummer. My advice...nurse your drink or lose your seat!

**Review: A Hidden Gem for Jazz and Cocktails**

I recently had the pleasure of visiting this spot- a newly opened jazz bar that effortlessly combines smooth tunes with expertly crafted cocktails. Tucked away in a cozy corner of the city, this place offers an intimate setting perfect for unwinding after a long day or for a special night out.

The ambiance is warm and inviting, with dim lighting, vintage decor, and plush seating that evokes a classic jazz club feel. The sound of live jazz fills the room, with talented musicians playing everything from bebop to soulful ballads. The acoustics are fantastic, allowing the music to be a centerpiece without overwhelming conversation.

The cocktail menu is a standout feature. Each drink is thoughtfully crafted, with a balance of creative flair and classic sensibility.

What sets them apart is the attention to detail—whether it’s the impeccable service, the beautifully garnished drinks, or the perfectly timed jazz sets. The staff is knowledgeable and attentive, happy to recommend drinks based on your preferences or to chat about the evening’s performers. Kiara and Ben were incredible! Can’t wait to see what they do with the place.

If you’re looking for a spot that offers the best of both worlds—delicious cocktails and authentic live jazz..It’s a refreshing addition to the local scene, and I’m excited to see it become a go-to destination for jazz lovers and cocktail enthusiasts alike.

Captivating, moody aesthetic that perfectly sets the stage for an intimate night out. The staff is warm and attentive, enhancing the overall experience with their genuine hospitality. Coupled with smooth live performances, it's a must-visit
